# AGENTS process (default ‚Äî no reminder needed)

Treat **every** coding task that changes `api/`, `web/`, Docker, or migrations as requiring the **full** workflow in **[`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md)**. The user should **not** have to type ‚Äúfollow the process‚Äù ‚Äî you run the deploy/verify steps yourself.

## Do by default (unless AGENTS.md says to skip)

1. **Always deploy** after changes that affect build or runtime: from the repo root run **`make dev-fast`** (preferred) or **`make dev`** ‚Äî **you** execute it every time; never end with ‚Äúrun compose yourself‚Äù when Docker can run. Prefer **`make dev-fast`** (Postgres + **tsx** watch + **Vite**, bind mounts) for day-to-day iteration. Use **`make dev`** when you need the **same single-container image** as production (**`web/dist`** + **`api/dist`** in the **`app`** image). Skip only for **docs-only** / **comment-only** with zero ship impact.
2. **Verify** the stack: e.g. `curl` **`/api/v1/health`** ‚Üí **200**, or **`docker compose ps`** (use the compose file you started).
3. **Tell the user the exact base URL**: after **`make dev-fast`**, **`http://localhost/`** when **`FAST_WEB_PORT`** is default **80**, else **`http://localhost:<FAST_WEB_PORT>/`**; after **`make dev`**, **`http://localhost/`** (port 80) or **`http://localhost:<HOST_PORT>/`**. If the classic image looks stale after **`make dev`**, run **`make dev-fresh`** and retry.
4. **`CHANGELOG.md`** ‚Äî add an **`[Unreleased]`** bullet in the **same** change when behaviour or build output changes; follow **[`changelog.mdc`](changelog.mdc)** skip rules.
5. **`docs/USER_GUIDE.md`** ‚Äî update when operator-visible UX, routes, or labels change; follow **[`user-documentation.mdc`](user-documentation.mdc)**.
6. **`git commit`** ‚Äî when the repo is Git, commit **each logical unit** with a short imperative message; follow **[`git-commits.mdc`](git-commits.mdc)**. Do not leave a large uncommitted diff unless the user asked to hold commits.

## What not to do

- Do not end a task with ‚Äúyou should run `make dev-fast`‚Äù / ‚Äúyou should run `make dev`‚Äù as the only action when you can run commands.
- Do not skip changelog because the user did not mention release notes.
- Do not assume hot reload when using **`make dev`** (compiled assets in the **`app`** image). **`make dev-fast`** does hot-reload source via bind mounts ‚Äî see **[`local-docker-deploy.mdc`](local-docker-deploy.mdc)**.

